{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% set nav = 'circle' %}

{% block title %}Get involved · Resources to join the Circle · Robinson Huron Treaty{% endblock %}
{% block description %}How to take part in the Circle: the one-page invitation, the transparency standard, the terms of reference, and how to join or make contact.{% endblock %}

{% block hero %}
<section class="hero">
  <div class="wrap wrap--wide">
    <p class="eyebrow">Bring your community in</p>
    <h1>Get involved.</h1>
    <p class="lead">Any beneficiary who shares these principles can take part. The idea is simple: bring one or two members from your community willing to be a local contact, and use the shared standard so every community asks the same plain questions in the same respectful way.</p>
  </div>
</section>
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <h2>Take five minutes</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Read the one-page invitation and the shared standard below.</li>
    <li>Find one or two members in your community willing to be a local contact.</li>
    <li>Make contact with the Circle so your community is represented on the joint letter.</li>
    <li>Put Part 2 of the standard to your own Chief and Council, and share what comes back.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Resources</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/rht-members-transparency-circle-onepager.pdf">The one-page invitation (PDF)</a>, the short version to print and share.</li>
    <li><a href="/standard">The shared transparency standard</a>, the common list of questions, treaty-wide and community level.</li>
    <li><a href="/circle">The Circle</a>, what the member-led movement is, its principles, and how it works.</li>
    <li><a href="/treaty-wide">The treaty-wide ask</a>, the joint letter to the Litigation Fund.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="card card--magenta">
    <h3>How to join or make contact</h3>
    <p>If you are a beneficiary of a Robinson Huron Treaty First Nation and you want your community represented, use the <a href="/contact">contact form</a> and a member will reply. You can also share this site and the one-page invitation with members in your community who would be willing to be a local contact.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="muted">Open to any member of a Robinson Huron Treaty First Nation who shares these principles: member-led, non-partisan, sourced facts framed as questions, no accusations, and no naming of private individuals.</p>
{% endblock %}
